			<div class="content" id="post-content-4175656">
									

<p>I've looked over several threads and pages, but have never found any records of this:</p>
<p>What if the Foundation contacts some of the other beings or extraterrestrials that are NOT hostile to Earth, and asks them to take SCP-682 away to their universe/dimension and dispose of it?</p>
<p>Some groups that they could ask:<br />
(The descriptions of these groups and others can be found here: <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-5887389/the-aliens-of-the-scp-universe">The Aliens of The SCP Universe</a>.</p>
<p><strong>The Showmen</strong>- (Canon Tales found here: <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/sotmhub">SOTM Canon</a><br />
According to one description I've read, these entities are &quot;willing to cut deals to help a civilization <em>IF</em> it makes for good TV.&quot;</p>
<p><strong>Halycon Light Beta</strong>- <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-3068">SCP-3068</a><br />
Although the citizens living here are not exactly friendly to the Foundation, doubtless some negotiation could be reached if the Foundation tried hard enough.</p>
<p>Doubtless there are many other non-Earth-based groups who have superior technology/weaponry and could deal with 682 far easier than the Foundation can. Has this idea been pursued?</p>

